  ;; gen-pos-coord, ratio/frac -> gen-unit-frac), so they generate valid
  ;; input and stay in coverage. No quarantine needed.)

  ;; (PolygonNodeTopology.isCrossing used to live here — RECOVERED 2026-06-01.
  ;; It expects five coords forming a valid polygon node (two edges a0->node->a1
  ;; and b0->node->b1 meeting at a shared node); independent random coords make
  ;; JTS's Quadrant throw. Fixed with gen-polygon-node (the structured 5-coord
  ;; tuple) supplied via :gen-tuple; port matches the oracle 0 mismatch / 400.
  ;; See the :hints below.)
  ;; (Octant.octant and Quadrant.quadrant used to live here — both RECOVERED
  ;; 2026-06-01. They throw on a zero vector / identical points (p0 == p1), and
  ;; gen-coord's 1e-10 magnitude clamp can collapse two independent draws to an
  ;; equal coordinate pair. Fixed with gen-distinct-coordinate-pair supplied as
  ;; the whole arg tuple via a :gen-tuple hint (c1 = c0 + non-zero offset); the
  ;; port matches the oracle 0 mismatch / 400 each. See the :hints below.)

