  ;; (returns JS null), so a null result passes through and matches the
  ;; oracle. Back in coverage.)

  ;; CONSTRUCTION-METHOD TIE-BREAK / REPRESENTATION — NOT a port bug. A
  ;; 2026-05-29 divergence investigation (N=1500/family, regular-vs-irregular
  ;; polygon inputs, discrete-Hausdorff + scalar-invariant cross-checks)
  ;; reclassified the construction families that failed the default
  ;; .norm/.equalsExact compare. None is a port logic bug, and none is FP
  ;; error in the OUTPUT value:
  ;;   - VariableBuffer / OffsetCurve / Densifier emit a GEOMETRICALLY
  ;;     IDENTICAL result (Hausdorff ~1e-14) that carries a near-coincident
  ;;     vertex the JVM JTS collapses; .equalsExact is vertex-count-strict,
  ;;     so it false-failed. (buffer(0) and a near-dup coordinate dedup do
  ;;     NOT reconcile them — only a same-shape predicate does.) Now compared
  ;;     via :compare :same-shape — back in coverage (validated 0 fail over
  ;;     the divergent population at N=1200/family).
  ;;   - MinimumClearance / SimpleMinimumClearance getLine, MinimumArea-
  ;;     Rectangle, DouglasPeucker / VW simplify, LargestEmptyCircle
  ;;     getRadiusLine return a NON-CANONICAL representative under the
  ;;     symmetric gen-wkt regular n-gons (every candidate feature tied):
  ;;     they agree on irregular inputs, and the scalar invariant the
  ;;     algorithm actually determines (clearance distance / rectangle area /
  ;;     circle radius) agrees to 1e-6. Now compared via :compare :length or
  ;;     :area — back in coverage. (The getDistance variants already passed.)
  ;; The per-method :compare assignments live in :hints below. CubicBezier-
  ;; Curve.bezierCurve is now back in coverage (re-classified 2026-06-01);
  ;; two entries stay quarantined.
  ;;   - CubicBezierCurve.bezierCurve (RECOVERED 2026-06-01): the earlier
  ;;     "FP-instability beyond 1e-6, extreme alpha crashes the port" reading
  ;;     did not hold up on direct testing. The Web-Image port collapses the
  ;;     three Java overloads into a single arity-3 JS function bezierCurve(
  ;;     geom, alpha, skew); the 2-arg and (Geometry, Geometry) forms are
  ;;     unreachable (a 2-arg call throws a CATCHABLE ClassCastException, not
  ;;     a crash). dedup-by-path already keeps the 3-arg overload (highest
  ;;     arity). Called with 3 args the port matches the JVM oracle to ~1e-15
  ;;     discrete-Hausdorff for every alpha up to 632, and never crashes at
  ;;     any alpha/skew tested (incl. 632/632). The only residual failures
  ;;     were a rare symmetric-difference overlay flake at unbounded (+-1000)
  ;;     alpha/skew. Bounding alpha to (0,1] and skew to [-1,1] via a
  ;;     :gen-overrides hint gives 0 fail over 400 samples; recovered with
  ;;     :compare :same-shape. See docs/plans/2026-05-29-divergence-followups.md.
  ;; (TopologyPreservingSimplifier.simplify and LargestEmptyCircle.getCenter
  ;; used to live here — both RECOVERED 2026-06-01, see the :hints below.
  ;;   - TopologyPreservingSimplifier.simplify: at tolerance >> extent the
  ;;     result collapses to a minimal topology-preserving triangle, and WHICH
  ;;     triangle is a tie-break under gen-wkt's regular n-gons; the tied
  ;;     triangles differ in both shape AND area, so neither :same-shape nor
  ;;     :area reconciles them (10/400 fail under :same-shape on regular
  ;;     input). Feeding an IRREGULAR (jittered-radius) polygon via
  ;;     :gen-overrides breaks the symmetry: 0/400 divergent. Now :gen-overrides
  ;;     {0 gen-irregular-wkt} + :compare :same-shape.
  ;;   - LargestEmptyCircle.getCenter: the center lies on a symmetric locus
  ;;     under regular obstacle/boundary polygons, so JTS and the port pick
  ;;     genuinely DIFFERENT tied centers (demonstrated: concentric pentagons,
  ;;     centers 117.5 apart) that no geometry compare reconciles. The only
  ;;     agreeing invariant is the clearance = distance(center, obstacles) =
  ;;     the LEC radius, identical at both tied centers. Now :compare
  ;;     :clearance. (The radius is also covered by getRadiusLine's :length;
  ;;     :clearance exercises the getCenter path directly.))

  ;; KNOWN DIVERGENCE — BufferResultValidator.isValidMsg returns a human-
  ;; readable String diagnostic; JTS and the wasmts port word the same
  ;; validity verdict differently, so a string-equality compare is the
  ;; wrong check (the isValid boolean is the real contract). TODO: compare
  ;; isValid, or drop the message compare.
  org.locationtech.jts.operation.buffer.validate.BufferResultValidator #{"isValidMsg"}

  ;; nearestPoints returns the closest point PAIR as a Coordinate[2];
  ;; coord-array-equal-form compares it order-strict. 2026-06-01 investigation:
  ;; the alleged seed-dependent pair-order divergence does NOT reproduce on the
  ;; current port — 0/400 over random gen-wkt and 0/3 over adversarial parallel-
  ;; segment / stacked-polygon tie provocations (JTS and the port pick the same
  ;; pair in the same order every time). Left quarantined because: (a) it can't
  ;; be reproduced-and-fixed, so un-quarantining with the strict compare risks a
  ;; rare unobserved flake, and (b) the Coordinate[] return is emitted by a
  ;; dedicated spec template (not generic-spec), so an order-insensitive
  ;; :compare override would need plumbing there, not the generic compare hook.
  ;; Recover by adding that override OR after a larger sample confirms 0 divergence.
  org.locationtech.jts.operation.distance.IndexedFacetDistance #{"nearestPoints"}
  org.locationtech.jts.operation.distance.DistanceOp #{"nearestPoints"}}

